                            <comment id="10510" author="mraible" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 03:47:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;An easy workaround is to specify an &quot;uploadTempDir&quot; property.  I&apos;d suggest fixing the problem in MockServletContext or simply documenting this workaround.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;multipartResolver&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
        class=&quot;org.springframework.web.multipart.commons.CommonsMultipartResolver&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;property name=&quot;uploadTempDir&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;value&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10511" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 04:41:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for spotting this - I&apos;ve adapted MockServletContext to use the JVM temp dir as ServletContext temp dir. Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
